    "Conditional group-exists empty-yes-arm boundary workloads keep one optional capture, one conditional site, and tiny haystacks so the scorecard measures helper-call overhead for the newly supported bounded empty-yes-arm conditional slice rather than regex throughput.",
    "Measured rows cover the bounded `a(b)?c(?(1)|e)` and `a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)|e)` compile/search/fullmatch plus constant-replacement `sub()`/`subn()` paths through module and compiled-`Pattern` entrypoints, the carry-forward fully-empty search row now also measures real timings, the bounded nested empty-yes-arm slice now times module and compiled-`Pattern` helpers across representative capture-present and capture-absent haystacks, the bounded quantified empty-yes-arm `(?:a(b)?c(?(1)|e)){2}` / `(?:a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)|e)){2}` module-search and `Pattern.fullmatch()` paths now time directly, and the bounded alternation-heavy empty-yes-arm `a(b)?c(?(1)|(e|f))` / `a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)|(e|f))` module-search and `Pattern.fullmatch()` paths now time directly while the accepted alternation-bearing fully-empty follow-on remains an explicit known gap in the fully-empty manifest until `RBR-0174` lands.",
    "Assertion-conditioned branches remain outside this benchmark manifest because CPython rejects them and the current benchmark harness only publishes timing rows for accepted syntax."
  ],
